## Coding conventions

- Type hints on every public function and class. `from __future__ import annotations` at top of every file.
- `_LOGGER = logging.getLogger(__name__)` per module. Never `print()` in committed code.
- No bare `except:` — specify exception classes.
- Constants module-level. No magic numbers in business logic.
- Async-only when needed. Don't introduce `asyncio` unless the workload demands it.

## Review guidelines

For Codex GitHub App + on-demand Claude Code Action reviewers.

P0 (block merge):
- Secrets, credentials, tokens in code, comments, or logs
- Removal of error handling on external API calls
- Hardcoded URLs, ports, or user identifiers

P1 (strong fix before merge):
- Missing tests on new public functions
- Bare `except:` / `except Exception:` without `_LOGGER.exception` or explicit re-raise
- `# type: ignore` without a `# reason:` comment
- `print()` in committed code
- Public API change without README update

P2 (nit):
- Naming drift, dead imports, style drift from this AGENTS.md

